@startuml slider_state_machine
' Created 2026-05-13: per claudeit/_diagram_amendments.md
!include dark-theme.puml
title Slider state machine per row (MonitorInfo.SliderState)\nTransitions verified at MonitorInfo.cs:49-112 + EnvironmentalCurveService.cs:336-347

state Enabled : user-owned slider drives DDC
state Disabled : group-excluded, no DDC writes
state CurveActive : curve drives DDC every tick
state CurveSleeping : curve holds, no DDC writes (disabled period)
state CurveReleased : user-released, curve does NOT resume\n(survives sleep cycles)
state Failed : DDC dead, slider greyed\n_preFailureSliderState stashed

[*] --> Enabled : new monitor, IsParticipating

Enabled --> Disabled : OnUserToggleOff (per-row icon click)
Enabled --> Failed : OnHardwareFailed (write/verify exhausted)
Enabled --> CurveActive : OnCurveEngaged(d=false) OR HarmonizeRow(d=false)
Enabled --> CurveSleeping : OnCurveEngaged(d=true) OR HarmonizeRow(d=true)

Disabled --> Enabled : OnUserToggleOn(c=false,d=false) [profile / per-row]
Disabled --> CurveActive : OnUserToggleOn(c=true,d=false)
Disabled --> CurveSleeping : OnUserToggleOn(c=true,d=true)
Disabled --> Failed : OnHardwareFailed

CurveActive --> CurveSleeping : HarmonizeRow(d=true)
CurveActive --> CurveReleased : OnUserRelease (drag / hotkey individual / disabled-period master drag)
CurveActive --> Enabled : OnCurveDisengaged
CurveActive --> Failed : OnHardwareFailed

CurveSleeping --> CurveActive : HarmonizeRow(d=false)
CurveSleeping --> CurveReleased : OnUserRelease
CurveSleeping --> Enabled : OnCurveDisengaged
CurveSleeping --> Failed : OnHardwareFailed

CurveReleased --> CurveActive : OnUserReengage(d=false) (double-click)
CurveReleased --> CurveSleeping : OnUserReengage(d=true)
CurveReleased --> Enabled : OnCurveDisengaged
CurveReleased --> Failed : OnHardwareFailed
note left of CurveReleased : HarmonizeRow EXPLICITLY preserves CR\n(default arm at EnvironmentalCurveService.cs:345)

Failed --> Enabled : OnHardwareRecovered(c,d)
note right of Failed
  OnHardwareRecovered now consults the live IsBrightnessCurveEnabledQuery
  + IsInDisabledPeriodQuery closures (post-H-03 fix). The recovery
  callsite at MonitorService promotes back through the correct
  arm (Enabled / CurveActive / CurveSleeping) without relying on
  the subsequent MonitorsRefreshed fan-out, eliminating the
  master-jitter symptom.
end note

' Post-fix notes on user-write paths
note as N_FIX_PATHS $TINT_GREEN
  Disabled-period master drag (post-H-04 fix):
   - BrightnessFlyout.ApplyMasterToEnabledMonitors now wraps the
     propagation in SuspendHardwareWrites, so individual writes
     during the master drag no longer fire OnUserRelease ->
     CurveActive -> CurveReleased. Enabled rows stay CA/CS across
     the master adjust.

  Hotkey adjust (post-H-05 fix):
   - App.xaml.cs hotkey paths (AdjustAllMonitorBrightness,
     AdjustNightLightBrightness, ApplyOrRestoreBrightness) now
     call NotifyUserBrightnessAdjustment first, matching the
     tray-scroll discipline. Hotkey individual writes route
     through the curve-release suppression window.
end note

' Dead helpers - documented for awareness, no transitions
note as N_DEAD
  OnSleepEnter / OnSleepExit at MonitorInfo.cs:107, 111 have
  ZERO callers. HarmonizeRow re-implements them inline plus the
  Enabled -> CurveActive promotion arm. Safe to remove.
end note

@enduml
